                            <comment id="13817910" author="ndimiduk" created="Sat, 9 Nov 2013 00:51:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You know for sure the issue is in the cans? Are you sure this isn&apos;t a dupe of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7743&quot; title=&quot;Replace *SortReducers with Hadoop Secondary Sort&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-7743&quot;&gt;HBASE-7743&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13818049" author="davelatham" created="Sat, 9 Nov 2013 07:14:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah - it&apos;s in the scans.  CopyTable doesn&apos;t use reducers at all.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13819449" author="stack" created="Mon, 11 Nov 2013 21:46:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this just a copytable config then &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=davelatham&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;davelatham&quot;&gt;Dave Latham&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13829104" author="davelatham" created="Thu, 21 Nov 2013 17:14:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think a new config option to call Scan.setBatch would do it.  I&apos;m always a bit puzzled about how scanner batching and caching interact with mixed length rows, but I imagine it would work out ok.  (4 years later, and still using a version where &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1996&quot; title=&quot;Configure scanner buffer in bytes instead of number of rows&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1996&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1996&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; didn&apos;t make it.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13829131" author="ndimiduk" created="Thu, 21 Nov 2013 17:46:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see TableInputFormat already supports overriding many scanner properties via config. Would it be sufficient to add another configuration point, &lt;tt&gt;hbase.mapreduce.scan.batchsize&lt;/tt&gt; perhaps?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13829145" author="ndimiduk" created="Thu, 21 Nov 2013 17:56:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=davelatham&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;davelatham&quot;&gt;Dave Latham&lt;/a&gt; will this patch work for you?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
